[section: demo]

[navigate: ${FILENAMES}]

[open-chat]

[new-chat]

A folder full of files with inconsistent names. Every team saves things differently.
Instead of cleaning this up by hand, let's turn the naming policy into a reusable skill.

[pause]

[prompt: Our company policy is to name files [company,customer,product file is about]-[MM_DD_YYYY]-[1-word-what-is-this].[extension]. Make a skill to properly name files using the creation date of the document.]

[wait]

Skill created. Before we run it, let's sharpen it.

[pause]

[prompt: Update the file-rename skill to use camel case for the 1-word descriptor.]

[wait]

Now let's put it to work.

[pause]

[select:all]

[prompt: Review these files to make sure they align to the company policy.]

[wait]

Every file that didn't match the policy got renamed. The ones that were already
correct were left alone. Let's go see the skill itself.

[pause]

[navigate: ${AGENT_ASSETS}]

There it is — a persistent skill anyone on this site can invoke. Not a flow, not a
macro. A reusable prompt that knows the naming convention. Next person who uploads
a file can run it in one click.

[pause]

[navigate: ${VIDEOS}]

[open-chat]

[new-chat]

Completely different use case. Someone uploaded a recording to SharePoint. Marketing
wants a YouTube description from it. Let's generate one.

[pause]

[prompt: Generate a youtube description for this file.]

[wait]

Done. Now let's make that repeatable as a Quick Step so anyone can run it on any
video without typing the prompt.

Add a Quick Step.

[pause]

[navigate: ${DOCS}]

[open-chat]

[new-chat]

Select the color palette document.

Last scenario. There's a brand color palette sitting in this library. Let's find out
what's in it — and then teach the AI to enforce it going forward.

[pause]

[prompt: Read this color palette. Tell me about the color palette it recommends.]

[wait]

The AI read the document and knows the palette. Now let's lock that in as a skill.

[pause]

[prompt: Create a skill that ensures anything we style uses this color palette.]

[wait]

Skill created. Let's go run it immediately!

[pause]

[navigate: ${LIST}]

[open-chat]

[new-chat]

[prompt: Make this view pretty.]

[wait]

The library view is now styled to the brand palette — without anyone looking up hex
codes or consulting the brand guidelines doc. The skill carries the knowledge.

[pause]

[screenshot: tools/screenshots/18-community-skills-walkthrough-final.png]

[section: reset]

[navigate: ${COMMUNITY}]

[open-chat]

[new-chat]

[prompt: Delete any skill related to file naming or renaming, if one exists.]

[wait]

Confirm the deletion in the browser if prompted.

[pause]

[new-chat]

[prompt: Delete any skill related to color palette or styling, if one exists.]

[wait]

Confirm the deletion in the browser if prompted.

[pause]

[navigate: ${FILENAMES}]

[new-chat]

[select:all]

[prompt: Delete all these files.]

[wait]

Confirm each deletion in the browser, then continue.

[pause]

Restoring the ten vendor contracts with their original messy filenames.

